INSERT INTO `eclipseguy_comments` VALUES (154,2296,'Mark','tarynmercury@yahoo.com.au','','115.128.27.14','2012-01-05 04:54:50','2012-01-05 08:54:50','Hey, Great information!\r\n\r\nMy wife and I are planning a trip from Sydney Australia around this time so we can check it out. A little confused about specific time though. We will be in Mt Shasta, Cali for it, though can\'t figure out what local time it will be. 1:20am doesn\'t seem right! Could you shed any light at all?\r\n\r\nLove the binoculars trick, im going to try that next time!!\r\n\r\nCheers\r\n\r\nMark',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-GB; rv:1.9.2.25) Gecko/20111212 Firefox/3.6.25 ( .NET CLR 3.5.30729)','',0,0),(8,1340,'Nicole','nicolestoffman@hotmail.com','http://www.myspace.com/nicolestoffman','99.233.179.89','2009-06-18 19:40:11','2009-06-18 23:40:11','Does Cat Stevens know about this?',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060215 Firefox/3.0.11','',0,0),(9,1096,'Alan Dyer','alandyer@telusplanet.net','http://backyardastronomy.com','208.70.62.14','2009-06-19 01:55:07','2009-06-19 05:55:07','Hi David,\r\n\r\nSo where are you planning to be July 22? I am assuming China? On your own or with a group? \r\n\r\nI prompted people to get to Shanghai, too, But then I wonder -- Can people really get into China on that short a notice -- are not visas required, passports cleared, etc that all takes time and bureaucracy? As an alternative, don\'t wait any longer to plan for where you want to be in 2010. The options for that eclipse are much more limited due to the scant landfall it makes, so available spots are filling up fast or are very costly -- i.e Easter Islanders charging the usual \"eclipse rates,\" making money while the Sun doesn\'t shine! But in many ways its an eclipse with better weather prospects and totality just as long for most places along the path. -- Alan Dyer',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_7; en-us) AppleWebKit/530.1