 One!'),(7818,3048,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(7856,3051,'eg_video_description_short','It looks fake but this is real!!!!  Totality in Antarctica.'),(7848,3050,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(7847,3050,'eg_media_related','a:4:{i:0;s:3:\"996\";i:1;s:3:\"590\";i:2;s:3:\"883\";i:3;i:3107;}'),(7846,3050,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(7820,3048,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(7881,3053,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(7882,3053,'eg_video_description_short','Watch the umbra move across Earth!'),(7883,3053,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(7884,3053,'eg_video_description_long','In this fast-motion, wide-angle shot of the eclipse in Yiwu, China, in 2008, we can clearly see the shadow of the Moon sweep across the Earth towards us - bathe us in its unearthly light - then sweep away from us at over 3000 kilometers per hour. You rarely get to see umbral action like this! Spine-tingling!'),(7897,3054,'eg_video_description_long','The \"Diamond Ring\" phase of a Total Eclipse signals the beginning of totality, and the end of totality. You get two Diamond Rings every eclipse! Watch both in this clip from the Total Eclipse in Zambia, Africa in 2001.'),(7894,3054,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(7895,3054,'eg_video_description_short','Watch two Diamond Rings in Zambia, Africa in 2001.'),(7896,3054,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(4488,3095,'_wp_attached_file','pathsign-200x200.jpg'),(7910,3055,'eg_video_description_long','In this clip from the Total Eclipse of December 2002 in the Outback, I have modified the speed and contrast in order to accentuate the movement of the Moon\'s shadow across the Earth. You don\'t get to see the Moon\'s umbra move like this everyday! Thanks to Klipsi for sharing his killer video.'),(7907,3055,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(7908,3055,'eg_video_description_short','Killer animation of the Moon\'s shadow sweeping through the sky!'),(7909,3055,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(4489,3095,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:200;s:6:\"height\";i:200;s:4:\"file\";s:20:\"pathsign-200x200.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:1:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:28:\"pathsign-200x200-150x150.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:0;}}'),(7924,3056,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(7923,3056,'eg_video_description_long','In the Australian Outback in 2002, the Total Eclipse happened just before sunset. When the Sun hit the western horizon, the Moon was still in the way! This was a once-in-a-lifetime experience. Thanks to Klipsi for sharing his killer video.'),(7922,3056,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(7921,3056,'eg_video_description_short','Watch an eclipsed sun set!'),(7920,3056,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(7933,3057,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(7934,3057,'eg_video_description_short','Total Eclipses on five continents in five minutes!  Great short!  Turn up the speakers for this!'),(7936,3057,'eg_video_description_long','This is my short documentary film about my life as an eclipse chaser. The film takes us to five solar eclipses on five continents in five minutes. It took over eight years to make! Seeking financing to make the 2-hour version! Anyone? For maximum value, turn up the speakers and go full-screen by clicking the arrows in the bottom right of the video.'),(7935,3057,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(4480,3094,'_eg_video_url','field_5543ea07053e4'),(7947,3058,'eg_video_description_short','The magnificent Terracotta Warriors!  Unique, behind-the-scenes footage - rarely seen like this.'),(7948,3058,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(7949,3058,'eg_video_description_long','During the eclipse expedition to China in 2008, we passed through the city of Xi\'an and had the chance to see the famous Terracotta Warriors. More than 8,000 warriors, horses and chariots have been uncovered.  They were created in 246 BC but not discovered until 1974. My invitation into the private area in the facility to film the warriors that are being repaired allowed me to get amazing, close up pictures of these sculptures.'),(4481,3094,'eg_video_url',''),(7962,3059,'eg_video_description_long','While most cameras are pointed at the sky during a Total Eclipse, the best way to get a sense of what it feels like to be there is to witness what is happening to the people on the ground. In this clip, watch as the Moon\'s shadow arrives, then retreats, from our observing spot - an ancient archeological site 1,000 feet above the Tigris River in Southern Turkey. So killer!'),(7959,3059,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(7960,3059,'eg_video_description_short','One of the best ways to get a sense of a Total Eclipse is not to watch the sky... but watch the people on the ground! Daytime turns into night before your eyes!'),(7961,3059,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(7977,3060,'eg_media_related','a:8:{i:0;s:3:\"649\";i:1;s:3:\"883\";i:2;s:3:\"590\";i:3;s:4:\"1750\";i:4;s:4:\"1574\";i:5;s:3:\"987\";i:6;s:4:\"1296\";i:7;i:3107;}'),(7972,3060,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(7973,3060,'eg_video_description_short','A life-long dream to go on safari in Africa comes true in 2001.  Eclipses rule.'),(7974,3060,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(7975,3060,'eg_video_description_long','After the TSE in Zambia in June, 2001, I went on Safari in Malawi. This clip is from the half-hour film I produced about the expedition.'),(7976,3060,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(7989,3061,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(7990,3061,'eg_media_related','a:5:{i:0;s:3:\"978\";i:1;s:3:\"981\";i:2;s:3:\"883\";i:3;s:3:\"590\";i:4;i:3107;}'),(7991,3061,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(7992,3061,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.com/wp-content/uploads/tripoli_vid_thumb.jpg'),(7993,3061,'_eg_video_duration','field_5543ea8d053e6'),(7994,3061,'eg_video_duration','4:57'),(7995,3061,'_eg_video_url','field_5543ea07053e4'),(7996,3061,'eg_video_url','http://player.vimeo.com/video/3245762'),(4472,3092,'eg_video_duration',''),(8031,3064,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.com/wp-content/uploads/img_2154.jpg'),(7998,3062,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(7999,3062,'eg_video_description_short','While mist and cloud can seriously diminish the corona, they don\'t have to kill the eclipse.  See the wicked, moody film from Moganshan, China, 22 July 2009.'),(8001,3062,'eg_video_description_long','Chasing the century\'s longest Total Eclipse to Asia during the Monsoon season is risky business.  Thousands of chasers across the region of totality were clouded out, while it poured rain on thousands more in Shanghai.  But in the little village of Moganshan - nestled on a hill in a bamboo forest - I saw one of the most mysterious sights I have ever seen:  the sky swallowing the eclipse with layer upon layer of mist.  Darkest eclipse I have ever seen - and one of the coolest experiences ever.'),(8000,3062,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8014,3063,'eg_video_description_long','A lot of media interest in my eclipse chasing was created when Toro Magazine published their account of my eclipse expedition to Libya in March 2006.  Cameron Phillips of CBC Radio in Vancouver called me up while I was at Burning Man that same year and invited me to speak on-air about my obsession.  Along with a few photos from the archive, here is the audio from the interview in its entirety.  Thanks to CBC.'),(8011,3063,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8012,3063,'eg_video_description_short','Eclipseguy on CBC Radio Canada in 2006 talking about what he loves best.'),(8013,3063,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(4473,3092,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(8024,3064,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8025,3064,'eg_video_description_short','If you have ever been fascinated with icebergs & glaciers - this film is for you.'),(8017,3063,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(8018,3063,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.com/wp-content/uploads/cbc_radio_thumb.jpg'),(8019,3063,'_eg_video_duration','field_5543ea8d053e6'),(8037,3065,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8038,3065,'eg_video_description_short','You have never seen the Sahara Desert like this.'),(8039,3065,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8040,3065,'eg_video_description_long','Part of my awesome eclipse chase to Libya in 2006 included bounding over orange sand dunes in 4x4s and camping in the desert with hardened local guides. Thought you might like to see what the Sahara Desert looks like - up close.'),(8041,3065,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(8042,3065,'eg_media_related','a:5:{i:0;s:3:\"981\";i:1;s:3:\"975\";i:2;s:3:\"883\";i:3;s:3:\"590\";i:4;i:3107;}'),(8043,3065,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(8052,3066,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8051,3066,'eg_video_description_short','This film is so killer you are crazy if you don\'t click on this link -  at least once.'),(8004,3062,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(8005,3062,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.com/wp-content/uploads/misty_vid_thumb.jpg'),(8006,3062,'_eg_video_duration','field_5543ea8d053e6'),(8064,3067,'eg_video_description_short','Penguins! If you aren\'t convinced yet that eclipse chasing can take you EVERYWHERE - then check this one out.'),(8065,3067,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8066,3067,'eg_video_description_long','In November 2003, I spent one month on a Russian icebreaker. Our team was the first in history to witness a Total Eclipse from the ice continent! This short film only begins to tell the story of how incredible this adventure was. And as you can see, we almost got clouded out for the eclipse!'),(8067,3067,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(8079,3068,'eg_video_description_long','As described in the Eclipse Film Database on this website, an episode of ER entitled \"When Night Meets Day\" employs a total solar eclipse. I\'ve put together the relevant scenes in this short clip so you can see how the eclipse was handled. Thanks to Warner Bros./NBC'),(8078,3068,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8076,3068,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8077,3068,'eg_video_description_short','Eclipses make it into the media all the time - with mixed results.  Check out the eclipse in this episode of ER.'),(7970,3059,'eg_video_url','http://player.vimeo.com/video/3246573'),(7971,3059,'_thumbnail_id','2161'),(7997,3061,'_thumbnail_id','2142'),(4451,3089,'_thumbnail_id','2135'),(8089,3069,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8090,3069,'eg_video_description_short','Come and fly with me into the Outback of Australia!  Awesome!'),(8092,3069,'eg_video_description_long','Flying into the middle of the Outback in Australia in a twin-prop Baron 58 with 4 friends in 2002 was one of the most outrageous eclipse chases ever! You have never seen dark skies until you have camped in the Outback! And the whopping 24 seconds of Total Eclipse was worth it all! This is adventure travel at its best.'),(8091,3069,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(4460,3090,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(4452,3090,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(8105,3070,'eg_video_description_long','In this unique time-lapse film from Billy Mallery, shot in Paraguana, Venezuela, in 1998, one frame was shot every 5 seconds over a period of 6 hours. Great results!'),(8104,3070,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8102,3070,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8103,3070,'eg_video_description_short','Unique time-lapse film shows the eclipse experience in a new light.  Filmed in Venezuela in 1998.'),(7958,3058,'_thumbnail_id','2146'),(4461,3090,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/taj_cu-200x138.jpg'),(8118,3071,'eg_video_description_long','Hundreds of still images are skillfully animated here by Canadian eclipse expert Andreas Gada, creating the only eclipse film in the world to show every phase of the eclipse. Shots taken in Jalu, Libya, 29 March 2006. Killer sequence!'),(8117,3071,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8115,3071,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8116,3071,'eg_video_description_short','Curious about what an entire TSE looks like - beginning to end?  Watch this unique film.'),(7953,3058,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.com/wp-content/uploads/warriors_vid_thumb.jpg'),(7954,3058,'_eg_video_duration','field_5543ea8d053e6'),(4449,3089,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(8131,3072,'eg_video_description_long','On November 23, 2003 - eclipse day in Antarctica - I was the only Canadian eclipse chaser aboard the Russian icebreaker Kapitan Khlebnikov. We had positioned ourselves on the ice shelf right in the path of totality. Minutes before the eclipse began, the Discovery Channel did this interview with me by satellite phone from the bow of the ship! Awesome day!'),(8130,3072,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8128,3072,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8129,3072,'eg_video_description_short','Watch my interview with Discovery Channel from the bow of the icebreaker in Antarctica!'),(7942,3057,'eg_video_duration','5:00'),(7943,3057,'_eg_video_url','field_5543ea07053e4'),(8141,3073,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8142,3073,'eg_video_description_short','On the way to the eclipse in Antarctica we saw some pretty amazing things.  Penguins!'),(8144,3073,'eg_video_description_long','Penguins are the coolest little animals.  Actually, the Emperors - made famous in film The March of the Penguins - are not that small!  Our expedition came across hundreds of Emperors by accident when we stopped the ship to hike to the \"blue diamond\" ice berg.  The shots of Adelie and Gentoo penguins are from other expeditions to the Antarctic Peninsula.'),(8143,3073,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(4450,3089,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/brazil_trip_thumb.jpg'),(8154,3074,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(7866,3051,'eg_video_url','http://player.vimeo.com/video/3269907https://vimeo.com/3269907'),(7867,3051,'_thumbnail_id','2151'),(7875,3052,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.com/wp-content/uploads/silk-road-new-thumb.jpg'),(8167,3075,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8168,3075,'eg_video_description_short','As far as eclipses in music videos go, this one is pretty cool.'),(7825,3048,'eg_video_duration','3:49'),(7826,3048,'_eg_video_url','field_5543ea07053e4'),(7827,3048,'eg_video_url','http://player.vimeo.com/video/3271641'),(8182,3076,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8181,3076,'eg_video_description_short','My talk at the TEDx Toronto Conference in September 2009.'),(8183,3076,'eg_video_description_long','TEDx Conferences are independently organized TED events held in cities  around the world that bring passionate speakers and presenters together  in a forum to spread their ideas.  In September 2009, I was asked to give a talk about what I have learned from a lifetime of chasing eclipses.  \"Understanding Ourselves In An Epic Universe\" is the result.  Lots of inspired talks on the main TED website <a href=\"http://www.ted.com/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.'),(8195,3077,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8196,3077,'eg_video_description_long','The eclipse that almost wasn\'t!  Freezing cold conditions - ice - snow - high winds - and a forecast of 90% overcast skies.  A thrilling chase.  And my first truly golden corona.  Check it out!  Full trip report &amp; pix <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.com/tripreport/south-america-–-11-july-2010\">here.</a>'),(8197,3077,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(8198,3077,'eg_media_related','a:5:{i:0;s:3:\"590\";i:1;s:3:\"608\";i:2;s:4:\"1574\";i:3;s:3:\"883\";i:4;i:3107;}'),(4437,3087,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/mexico_logo2_01-166x200.jpg'),(8209,3078,'eg_video_description_long','The mystique of the desert of the American southwest hung in the air with the eclipsed sun as we chased the Annular Eclipse of May 20, 2012, south of the Grand Canyon in Arizona.  Best eclipse video ever!  Turn up the speakers and go Full Screen!\n\n<span style=\"color: #71767a; font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: 21px; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: #f4f5f7; display: inline ! important; float: none;\">\n</span>'),(8208,3078,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8206,3078,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8207,3078,'eg_video_description_short','Great Documentary Film.\nThe expedition to chase the Annular eclipse in Arizona in May 2012 went spectacularly well!  A must see!!'),(7799,3046,'eg_video_duration','1:20'),(7800,3046,'_eg_video_url','field_5543ea07053e4'),(7783,3045,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(8219,3079,'_eg_video_description_short','field_55443984c0e42'),(8220,3079,'eg_video_description_short','TV Producers seem endlessly fascinated with solar eclipses - frequently using them as narrative devices that drive dramatic storylines.  Here is a terrific example.'),(8221,3079,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8222,3079,'eg_video_description_long','In the 2011 episode \"Partial Eclipse of the Heart\" from the TV series \"Being Human,\" the writers employ a Total Eclipse of the Sun to super-charge the supernatural.  When the eclipse takes place - the characters are caught off guard - and the dead return to the earthly plane to confront the assailants that \"shredded\" them.\n\nFollowing in the classic mythos of eclipses, as used in the 1986 film \"Ladyhawke,\" the few brief moments of totality creates an ethereal pocket in space and time where dearly departed lovers are given a final chance to reconnect, face to face, before facing eternity apart.\n\nAs far as treatments go, there is nothing much new here.  But the nod to the classical treatment has a lot of credibility in my opinion, and the computer-generated visuals of the celestial phenomena are first rate - especially when you take into account how poorly eclipses are usually depicted in film.  Kudos to the producers.\n\nDon\'t miss the <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.com/eclipse-film-database\">Eclipse Film Database</a> on this website.  The world\'s only comprehensive database of eclipses in documentary and dramatic films.\n\nBeing Human © All rights reserved by the producers.  Clips courtesy of BH2 Productions (Muse Entertainment) Inc., Kodiak Media, USA.'),(8235,3080,'eg_video_description_long','We were supposed to be on the beach at our luxurious villa for this eclipse!  But that\'s where all the clouds were.  We ran inland - slept in our cars - and awoke to more cloud.  We ran again.  Our third site was perfectly clear.  This is what we saw.  Actual Totality observed from this location was 1:28 min. '),(8234,3080,'_eg_video_description_long','fie