totality is observed. Best total eclipse sequence ever! I\'m not trying to make you jealous! Honest! If you only ever get to see a total eclipse on the internet you haven\'t lived yet!'),(8106,3070,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(8119,3071,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(8145,3073,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(8155,3074,'eg_video_description_short','Is this 1986 offering from Peter Gabriel the first music video to employ a Total Eclipse?'),(8156,3074,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8157,3074,'eg_video_description_long','This 1986 music video for Gabriel\'s beautiful song \"Don\'t Give Up\' was directed by Godley &amp; Creme, the English pop music duo that began releasing albums together after splitting from the band 10cc.  Musically, they were known for their ground-breaking production work.  But their greatest success came as the innovative directors of more than 50 music videos in the 1980s.  This video is one, long shot - and features Gabriel and Bush in a never-ending embrace as the Moon totally eclipses the Sun behind them.'),(8169,3075,'_eg_video_description_long','field_554439565a880'),(8170,3075,'eg_video_description_long','From the album An End Has a Start, set in a sterile suburbia, the members of the band Editors play while a small child draws a large chalk circle in the middle of the street and makes the Sun disappear behind the Moon - along with all the neighbourhood\'s inhabitants!  Wins a prize for the most hard-edged filmic eclipse!'),(8172,3075,'eg_media_related','a:2:{i:0;s:4:\"1296\";i:1;i:3107;}'),(8171,3075,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(8184,3076,'_eg_media_related','field_5543ef17453fe'),(7823,3048,'eg_media_thumbnail_url','http://eclipseguy.com/wp-content/uploads/baja91_vid_thumb.jpg'),(8199,3077,'_eg_media_thumbnail_url','field_5543eaa4053e7'),(7782,3045,'eg_media_related','a:6:{i:0;s:3:\"883\";i:1;s:3:\"614\";i:2;s:3:\"600\";i:3;s:3:\"967\";i:4;s:3:\"981\";i:5;i:3107;}'