n a private charter aircraft out of Argentina that will fly into the eclipse at 35,000 feet!  We are guaranteed clear skies!   <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/news/one-seat-available-eclipse-observation-flightpatagoniajuly-2010\">Click here for details.</a>\r\n\r\nFor more on this eclipse, visit Fred Espenak\'s dedicated NASA web page <a href=\"http://eclipse.gsfc.nasa.gov/SEmono/TSE2010/TSE2010.html\" target=\"_blank\">here.</a>','Total Solar Eclipse of 11 July 2010',0,'This is the next big one! ','inherit','open','open','','1521-revision-22','','','2010-06-11 18:19:10','2010-06-11 22:19:10','',1521,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/1521-revision-22',0,'revision','',0),(1732,5,'2010-01-17 16:48:55','2010-01-17 20:48:55','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ase2010globe1a.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1669 aligncenter\" title=\"ase2010globe1a\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ase2010globe1a-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"ase2010globe1a\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>In red the path of the Annular Eclipse.</blockquote>\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/2010_annular_eclipse_1000.jpg\"><img class=\"size-thumbnail wp-image-1667 alignleft\" title=\"2010_annular_eclipse_1000\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/2010_annular_eclipse_1000-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"2010_annular_eclipse_1000\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis is what you would have seen in the sky on 15 January 2010 if you were anywhere in the path of annularity.  I wasn\'t - saving for July!! But thousands gathered along the eclipse path to see the millennium\'s longest eclipse.\r\n\r\nIf you missed it, here is a list of links to photos and reports: \r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.spaceweather.com/eclipses/gallery_15jan10.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Space Weather</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sonnenfinsternis2010.de/index.htm#berichte\" ta