e window where the eclipse will be visible above Earth\'s western horizon.  As of 15 January 2010, I have one seat available in the row where the plane\'s wing will be visible.  The wing creates no blind spot for the eclipse itself, but obviously removes a portion of the sky from view.  These are the least expensive seats on the aircraft, with the \"no wing\" seats costing the most.  This seat is available now for €499/USD715. If you are interested, post a comment here or contact me by email.  This seat will not be available for long!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.eclipse-city.com/eclipse,patagonia,10087.html\" target=\"_blank\">Eclipse City</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/091218_observation-flight.pdf\">Download Seating Plan</a>\r\n\r\nYou have to get yourself to El Calafate, Argentina, by 11 July 2010.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/2010_eclipse_flight_path.jpg\"></a><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/2010_eclipse_flight_path2.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1716 aligncenter\" title=\"Microsoft Word - July 2009 Patagonia English\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/2010_eclipse_flight_path2.jpg\" alt=\"Microsoft Word - July 2009 Patagonia English\" width=\"450\" height=\"375\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\nWith South Pacific cruises either cost-prohibitive or completely sold out, and Easter Island already packed to the rafters, this is definitely the most exciting and cost-effective option left.  And you don\'t have to worry about the weather!  This flight will travel well above any threatening clouds and we are guaranteed a spectacular observation in crystal clear skies. We will see approximately 2:55 of Totality.\r\n\r\nYou must see a Total Eclipse of the Sun from the air before you die!','ONE SEAT AVAILABLE! Eclipse Observation Flight/Patagonia/July 2010.',0,'I have one seat available on an exclusive eclipse observation flight from Patagonia, 11 July 2010.  Com