'attachment','image/png',0),(516,4,'2009-03-08 22:26:05','2009-03-09 02:26:05','','thumbnail-magnetosphere',0,'','inherit','open','open','','thumbnail-magnetosphere','','','2009-03-08 22:26:05','2009-03-09 02:26:05','',287,'http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/wp-content/uploads/thumbnail-magnetosphere.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(533,5,'2009-03-15 22:10:25','2009-03-16 02:10:25','','Photo Galleries',0,'','inherit','open','open','','334-revision-5','','','2009-03-15 22:10:25','2009-03-16 02:10:25','',334,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/334-revision-5',0,'revision','',0),(534,5,'2009-03-15 22:21:43','2009-03-16 02:21:43','','Photo Galleries',0,'','inherit','open','open','','334-revision-6','','','2009-03-15 22:21:43','2009-03-16 02:21:43','',334,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/334-revision-6',0,'revision','',0),(3107,4,'2015-04-11 20:55:37','2015-04-12 00:55:37','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>My 21st Solar Eclipse Expedition</strong></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>My 14th Total Eclipse of the Sun</strong></p>  <blockquote><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/tse2015-globe-view1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2969 aligncenter\" alt=\"tse2015 globe view1\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/tse2015-globe-view1.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"399\" /></a> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"> My first Total Eclipse from a plane!</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TSE2015_flightpath.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2845 aligncenter\" alt=\"TSE2015_flightpath\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TSE2015_flightpath.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"572\" /></a>Dusseldorf to Dusseldorf - via the best view in the world!</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00834.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2972 aligncenter\" alt=\"DSC00834\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00834.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">We check in about 6am for our special flight to totality. There are over 15 eclipse flights today!</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00836.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2973\" alt=\"DSC00836\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00836.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Veteran chasers get boarding passes after years of planning.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00841.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2974\" alt=\"DSC00841\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00841.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"497\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Pretty stoked to see my 21st eclipse!</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00842.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2975 aligncenter\" alt=\"DSC00842\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00842.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is my first trip to a Point that doesn\'t exist!</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00867.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2976 aligncenter\" alt=\"DSC00867\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00867.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"477\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">eclipseguy with Glenn Schneider from The Steward Observatory at the University of Arizona. Glenn is the Project Lead - he makes the calculations for our Totality Run: the aircraft\'s interception of the Moon\'s umbra.  He\'s seen 32 Total Solar Eclipses!</p> </blockquote> <!--nextpage--> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00868.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2978 aligncenter\" alt=\"DSC00868\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00868.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"440\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is the Boeing 737-800 taking us to 37,000 ft.</p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/sofi2015-08.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3014\" alt=\"sofi2015-08\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/sofi2015-08.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">High tech stabilization techniques!</p> </blockquote> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Frame Grabs from the Video</strong></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.45.15-PM.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2979 aligncenter\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-03-30 at 6.45.15 PM\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.45.15-PM.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"339\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Look how much room we have!  I love flying like this.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.43.26-PM.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2980 aligncenter\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-03-30 at 6.43.26 PM\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.43.26-PM.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"335\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Chasers invent all kinds of specialized gear to shoot totality from up here.  The restraints are considerable!</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.44.30-PM.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2981 aligncenter\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-03-30 at 6.44.30 PM\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.44.30-PM.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"335\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.46.46-PM.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2982 aligncenter\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-03-30 at 6.46.46 PM\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.46.46-PM.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"337\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3016\" alt=\"sofi2015-27\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/sofi2015-27.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"330\" /></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.48.04-PM.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2983 aligncenter\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-03-30 at 6.48.04 PM\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.48.04-PM.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"336\" /></a>You can see increased detail in the solar corona if you \'dark adapt\' your dominant eye before totality begins.  There were lots of pirates on board!</p> </blockquote> <!--nextpage--> <p style=\"text-align: left;\">Over a lifetime of eclipse chasing, it\'s not uncommon to have a few eclipses that are missed because of bad weather or equipment failure or any of the other contingencies that fall under Murphy\'s Law.  And I have been very lucky!  I always see the eclipse and my shots always turn out.  But I am a little disappointed with my images from the GoPro camera I mounted at the window in Row 12.  Ice Crystals built up as we climbed higher and drew closer to totality.  By our Totality Run, there was almost no space on the window that didn\'t look like I was shooting through a heavy sprinkling of icing sugar. Gulp.  As a result, the images are all dirty - something we tried hard to avoid by cleaning the windows thoroughly on the ground.  But they are all I\'ve got!  Still, the incredible and almost frightening approach of the Moon\'s shadow from behind us is still discernible.</p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_1.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2984 aligncenter\" alt=\"gopro_1\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_1.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">At 37,000 ft. above the North Sea between Norway and Iceland, the aircraft positions itself precisely in the same direction of travel as the advancing umbral shadow that is being projected on to the Earth by the eclipsing Moon.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_2.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2985 aligncenter\" alt=\"gopro_2\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_2.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">As totality nears, you can clearly see the darkening on the horizon to the south as the monstrous, dark shadow of the Moon races to engulf us from behind.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_3.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2986 aligncenter\" alt=\"gopro_3\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_3.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">At the precise moment predicted, the advancing edge of the Moon\'s shadow is projected on to the Earth at our location.  Totality begins!  And a full set of goosebumps to boot!</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_4.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2987 aligncenter\" alt=\"gopro_4\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_4.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"339\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">At mid-totality, the curved aspect of the shadow is evident as it extends through the sky.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_5.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2988 aligncenter\" alt=\"gopro_5\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_5.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Traveling at about 3,000 kph., the Moon\'s shadow inevitably overtakes us, and the trailing edge of the shadow cone can now be seen beneath us.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_6.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2989 aligncenter\" alt=\"gopro_6\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/gopro_6.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Totality ends with the reappearance of the Sun\'s photosphere, and the trailing edge of the umbra can be seen racing off towards Svalbard and the North Pole.</p> </blockquote> <!--nextpage--> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TSE2015_1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2991 aligncenter\" alt=\"TSE2015_1\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TSE2015_1.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"399\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">My frame-grab of the Diamond Ring that starts totality!</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TSE2015_2.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2992 aligncenter\" alt=\"TSE2015_2\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TSE2015_2.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"399\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Mid-Totality and the corona at its peak.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/sofi2015-15.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3015\" alt=\"sofi2015-15\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/sofi2015-15.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></a></p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.55.51-PM.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2993 aligncenter\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-03-30 at 6.55.51 PM\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.55.51-PM.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"336\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">When its over its time for champagne and the unveiling of Craig Small\'s eclipse flag, a sign that bodes well for clear skies at the next eclipse!</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_3486A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3033\" alt=\"IMG_3486A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/IMG_3486A.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></a></p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.49.30-PM.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2994 aligncenter\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-03-30 at 6.49.30 PM\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Screen-Shot-2015-03-30-at-6.49.30-PM.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">A most curious flight plan!  The straight edge of the flight path to the west was our Totality Run.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2953 aligncenter\" alt=\"TSE_2015_GROUP_PHOTO_600\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TSE_2015_GROUP_PHOTO_600.jpeg\" width=\"600\" height=\"235\" /></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">The team that made it happen on 20 March 2015.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Malicki_totality_600.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2995 aligncenter\" alt=\"Malicki_totality_600\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Malicki_totality_600.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"399\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Chris Malicki shared Row 12 with me and got this great image.</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\">There were scores of great images and videos to come out of this eclipse - from the air and from land.  Check out these additional reports from chasers around the world.</p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://nicmosis.as.arizona.edu:8000/ECLIPSE_WEB/TSE2015/TSE2015_REPORT.html\" target=\"_blank\">Glenn Schneider\'s report</a></p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://sites.williams.edu/iau-eclipses/svalbard-eclipse-2015/\" target=\"_blank\">Williams College Expedition Svalbard</a></p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.twanight.org/newTWAN/photos.asp?ID=3004990\" target=\"_blank\">Tunc Tezel Photo</a></p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.eclipseland.com/europa-2015-total.html\" target=\"_blank\">Stephan Hiensius Eclipseland</a></p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://skyweek.wordpress.com/2015/03/19/live-blog-zur-sonnenfinsternis-vom-20-marz/\" target=\"_blank\">Daniel Fisher Blog1</a>  <a href=\"https://skyweek.wordpress.com/2015/03/23/nova-sgr-2015-no-2-erreichte-4-mag-fallt-nun/\" target=\"_blank\">Daniel Fisher Blog2</a></p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/122849251\" target=\"_blank\">Martin Junius Video</a></p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yjibg3jWx_4&amp;feature=youtu.be\" target=\"_blank\">Guillaume Cannat Video</a></p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://apod.nasa.gov/apod/ap150331.html\" target=\"_blank\">Composite Photo of the Corona March 20, 2015</a></p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://nordlandseite.de/berichte/reise/sonnenfinsternis2015.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Thomas Bujack Report</a>  Thanks for the pictures!</p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\">Wanna come eclipse chasing?  <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/eclipse-calendar\">See where we are headed next</a>.</p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>','By Air above The Norwegian Sea - 20 March 2015',0,'The monstrous black shadow stuns chasers at 37,000 ft with never-before-seen views. At 600 mph this is eclipse chasing!','publish','closed','closed','','by-air-above-the-norwegian-sea-20-march-2015','','','2015-04-11 20:55:37','2015-04-12 00:55:37','',0,'http://eclipseguy.dev/reports/by-air-above-the-norwegian-sea-20-march-2015',0,'reports','',0),(527,5,'2008-10-10 18:51:31','2008-10-10 22:51:31','','Media Vault',0,'','inherit','open','open','','285-revision-23','','','2008-10-10 18:51:31','2008-10-10 22:51:31','',285,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/285-revision-23',0,'revision','',0),(528,5,'2009-03-10 01:55:37','2009-03-10 05:55:37','','Media Vault',0,'','inherit','open','open','','285-revision-24','','','2009-03-10 01:55:37','2009-03-10 05:55:37','',285,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/285-revision-24',0,'revision','',0),(529,5,'2009-03-10 01:56:00','2009-03-10 05:56:00','','Media Vault',0,'','inherit','open','open','','285-revision-25','','','2009-03-10 01:56:00','2009-03-10 05:56:00','',285,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/285-revision-25',0,'revision','',0),(530,5,'2008-09-08 08:58:21','2008-09-08 12:58:21','Click on the following links blah blah blah lorem ipsum\r\n<a title=\"La Paz\" href=\"http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/wp/trip-reports/la-paz/\" target=\"_self\">La Paz Mexico</a>','Trip Reports',0,'','inherit','open','open','','3-revision-6','','','2008-09-08 08:58:21','2008-09-08 12:58:21','',3,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/3-revision-6',0,'revision','',0),(545,5,'2009-03-15 22:42:37','2009-03-16 02:42:37','Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side. Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side. Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side.Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side. Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side. Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side.Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side. Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side. Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side.','Shots from Zambia',0,'Baja California Sur, Mexico, is the thin peninsula that extends south of the state of California along mainland Mexico\'s Paciï¬c side.','inherit','open','open','','467-revision-3','','','2009-03-15 22:42:37','2009-03-16 02:42:37','',467,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/467-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(551,4,'2009-03-23 04:37:05','2009-03-23 08:37:05','Where will you be?\r\n<h3>2015</h3>\r\n<strong>March 20</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 2:47. North Pole. Norwegian Sea.\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"TSE2015animation\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2015Mar20T.GIF\" />\r\n<strong>September 13</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. S. Africa. Antarctica.\r\n<h3>2016</h3>\r\n<strong>March 9</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 4:09. Sumatra, Borneo, Sulawesi, Pacific Ocean.\r\n<img alt=\"sinclair animation 2016\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2016Mar09T.GIF\" />\r\n<strong>September 1</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Africa. Indian Ocean.\r\n<h3>2017</h3>\r\n<strong>February 26</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Pacific. Chile. Argentina. Atlantic. Africa.\r\n\r\n<strong>August 21</strong> - THE GREAT AMERICAN ECLIPSE! TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 2:40. United States. Atlantic Ocean. Visit <a href=\"http://greatamericaneclipse.com\" target=\"_blank\">greatamericaneclipse.com</a> for more.\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"sinclair animation 2017\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2017Aug21T.GIF\" />\r\n<h3>2018</h3>\r\n<strong>February 15</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. Antarctica.  South America.\r\n\r\n<strong>July 13</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. Australia.\r\n\r\n<strong>August 11</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. Europe.  Asia.\r\n<h3>2019</h3>\r\n<strong>July 2</strong> - TOTAL  Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 4:37. South Pacific. Chile. Argentina.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2019Jul02T.gif\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2837\" alt=\"SE2019Jul02T\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2019Jul02T.gif\" width=\"250\" height=\"270\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>December 26</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Saudi Arabia.  India.  Sumatra.  Borneo.\r\n<h3>2020</h3>\r\n<strong>June 21</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Africa. South Asia.  China.  Pacific.\r\n\r\n<b>December 14</b> - TOTAL  Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 2:13. South Pacific. Chile. Argentina. South Atlantic.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2020Dec14T.gif\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2836\" alt=\"SE2020Dec14T\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2020Dec14T.gif\" width=\"250\" height=\"270\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipse.gsfc.nasa.gov/SEdecade/SEdecade2021.html\" target=\"_blank\">More eclipses ... </a>','Eclipse Calendar',0,'','publish','open','open','','eclipse-calendar','','','2015-03-12 18:47:15','2015-03-12 22:47:15','',0,'http://eclipseguy.dev/?page_id=551',0,'page','',1),(2827,5,'2014-02-07 21:59:13','2014-02-08 01:59:13','Must-see from this eclipse: <a href=\"http://www.zam.fme.vutbr.cz/~druck/eclipse/\" target=\"_blank\">Miloslav Druckmüller\'s</a> outstanding photographs\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/africa_location_map.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2789 aligncenter\" alt=\"africa_location_map\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/africa_location_map.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Pokwero, Uganda</p>\r\nOn 3 November 2013 thousands of chasers from around the world gathered along the eclipse path in central Africa to see a truly unique event:  what is called a \"hybrid\" or \"transitional\" eclipse.   This means the size of the Moon wasn\'t quite large enough to completely cover the Sun - a Total Eclipse - and it wasn\'t quite small enough to slip inside the Sun - an Annular Eclipse.  On this day, the disc of the Moon was identical in size to the disc of the Sun creating an absolutely perfect match in the sky. The arrangement created some stunning magic for the lucky few who had clear skies.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/group-set-up.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2787 aligncenter\" alt=\"group set up\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/group-set-up.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Setting up in Uganda 03 November 2013.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\nI missed this one!  Yikes!  One of the few that got away.  But considering I had just returned home from two weeks in Nepal on a community development mission - I wasn\'t complaining.  My good friend Lukas Gornisiewicz made the trek to Pokwero, Uganda, and got some great images.  His was one of the few expeditions that was successful.  Up and down the eclipse path, chasers were met with sand storms and clouds and wind.  Dozens of expeditions - thousands of people - went all that way and didn\'t see the eclipse.  Yes - a chaser\'s nightmare.  But such was the case in November 2013 - and something you have to accept if you wanna chase eclipses.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TotalityWideAngle02.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2786 aligncenter\" alt=\"TotalityWideAngle02\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/TotalityWideAngle02.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">So close to being clouded out!</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<!--nextpage-->\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/lukas-chromo-ring.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2785 aligncenter\" alt=\"lukas chromo ring\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/lukas-chromo-ring.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A Ring of Chromosphere! This is never seen at typical Total Solar Eclipses. Just Stunning!\r\nphoto Lukas Gornisiewicz</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h6 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h6>\r\n<a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/totality-sidebar-e1391822176803.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2788 aligncenter\" alt=\"totality sidebar\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/totality-sidebar-e1391822176803.jpg\" width=\"613\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A stunning sequence by Ben Cooper <a href=\"http://launchphotography.com\" target=\"_blank\">Launchphotography.com</a></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">These images were taken by Ben Cooper aboard a private biz jet out of Bermuda that flew into the Moon\'s shadow over the Atlantic before its rendezvous in Africa. From 44,000 ft. the view was spectacular - free from clouds and the perils of weather.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/multi-bead-cu.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2783 aligncenter\" alt=\"multi bead cu\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/multi-bead-cu.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Not quite Total, not quite Annular.  100% amazing.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Check out this amazing vid from Stephan Heinsius at 44,000 ft.</p>\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/78660927\" height=\"375\" width=\"600\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/78660927\">B014 TSE2013</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/user22429055\">Stephan Heinsius</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\nThis was one for the record books!  Can\'t believe I wasn\'t there!  Doh!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Heartbreak & Joy in Africa',0,'Although many chased, only a select few actually got to see this unique eclipse, 03 November 2013','inherit','open','open','','2779-revision-v1','','','2014-02-07 21:59:13','2014-02-08 01:59:13','',2779,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/2779-revision-37',0,'revision','',0),(552,5,'2009-03-23 04:37:01','2009-03-23 08:37:01','','Eclipse Calendar',0,'','inherit','open','open','','551-revision','','','2009-03-23 04:37:01','2009-03-23 08:37:01','',551,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/551-revision',0,'revision','',0),(563,4,'2009-03-01 23:57:47','2009-03-02 03:57:47','This is a gallery of photos from Jalu.\r\n\r\nZOMG awesome.','Photos From Jalu',0,'This is a gallery of photos from Jalu. I took them with a camera, because I\'m just awesome like that.','inherit','open','open','','465-revision-3','','','2009-03-01 23:57:47','2009-03-02 03:57:47','',465,'http://eclipseguy.dev/un