setting the <strong>\"Blog pages show at most\"</strong> setting to <strong>1</strong> under \'reading\' in the admin panel is a hack-y fix for this issue - pagination on pages using a custom query now seems to work. I\'ve only tested this when the query is only affecting `showposts`, but it\'s working so far.Â  Promising.<br/><br/>\r\nI\'ve posted this at <br/><a href=\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/167795?replies=6#post-875258\" target=\"_blank\">http://wordpress.org/support/topic/167795?replies=6#post-875258</a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>','Home',0,'','inherit','open','open','','352-revision-v1','','','2008-10-13 08:46:17','2008-10-13 12:46:17','',352,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/352-revision-14',0,'revision','',0),(567,4,'2008-10-09 23:32:33','2008-10-10 03:32:33','','Links',0,'','inherit','open','open','','346-revision-3','','','2008-10-09 23:32:33','2008-10-10 03:32:33','',346,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/346-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(568,5,'2008-10-09 23:37:49','2008-10-10 03:37:49','Testing grounds for the new Eclipseguy.com site.  Hola iMoon!\r\n\r\n','About',0,'','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-5','','','2008-10-09 23:37:49','2008-10-10 03:37:49','',2,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/2-revision-5',0,'revision','',0),(569,5,'2009-03-30 18:24:07','2009-03-30 22:24:07','Testing grounds for the new Eclipseguy.com site.  Hola iMoon!\r\n\r\n','About',0,'','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-6','','','2009-03-30 18:24:07','2009-03-30 22:24:07','',2,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/2-revision-6',0,'revision','',0),(570,4,'2009-03-29 19:08:15','2009-03-29 23:08:15','<strong>Development Notes.</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Need to sort out how to tackle tabbed nav in media section</li>\r\n	<li>ascertain how to pull individual media pages through into aggregator page. (look into category pull-through)</li>\r\n	<li>sort out menu cascades</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - worked out method of using custom fields to store video embed codes and details.Â  This will be useful when pulling video meta data through into other pages.Â  Awesome.</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 10 - <span style=\"color: #999999;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\"><span>***need to figure out how to recurse through an array in PHP*** </span>in order to automatically grab all \"vid-related\" field data and spit it out in the \"vid-permalink\" template.</span></span> This has been accomplished <a href=\"http://test.rubbersuit.com/eclipseguy/media-vault/video/vid-permalink-01\" target=\"_self\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li>oct 11 - determined that using custom wp_query is the trick to customizing the output of the page loop.Â  This is in place on home.php currently.</li>\r\n	<li>oct 12 - discovered bug in wordpress which show up if:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>using custom permalink structure</li>\r\n	<li>using custom query to generate page content</li>\r\n	<li>showposts variable in query doesn\'t match settings in master \'read\' settings in admin panel</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe workaround seems to be making sure that the \'read\' settings agree with the showposts var in the query.  This poses a limitation to having different queries on different pages that are paginated.  It doesn\'t, however, affect non-paginated custom queries, so we should be able to work around it.  Bummer though.\r\n\r\nMy delicious bookmarks contain some links that cover this issue.</li>\r\n	<li>oct. 13 - <span style=\"color: #00ccff;\">may have a solution to the </span><span style=\"color: #00ccff;\">above!!!</span> looks like setting the <strong>\"Blog pages show at most\"</strong> setting to <strong>1</strong> under \'reading\' in the admin panel is a hack-y fix for this issue - pagination on pages using a custom query now seems to work. I\'ve only tested this when the query is only affecting `showposts`, but it\'s working so far.Â  Promising.\r\n\r\nI\'ve posted this at\r\n<a href=\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/167795?replies=6#post-875258\" target=\"_blank\">http://wordpress.org/support/topic/167795?replies=6#post-875258</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Home',0,'','inherit','open','open','','352-revision-v1','','','2009-03-29 19:08:15','2009-03-29 23:08:15','',352,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/352-revision-15',0,'revision','',0),(586,5,'2009-04-06 01:38:00','2009-04-06 05:38:00','','thumb_totality_in_turkey',0,'','inherit','open','open','','thumb_totality_in_turkey','','','2009-04-06 01:38:00','2009-04-06 05:38:00','',0,'http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/thumb_totality_in_turkey.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3106,4,'2013-02-17 04:03:48','2013-02-17 08:03:48','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">My 18th Solar Eclipse Expedition My second successfully-observed Annular Eclipse!</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"dm in the field1\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00607A_01.jpg\" /></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is what my Front Row Seat on the Universe looked like in Arizona in May 2012!</p> <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/arizona_location.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2708 aligncenter\" alt=\"arizona_location\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/arizona_location.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">The region around Grand Canyon National Park is an ideal eclipse location on the Earth.  Sunny and dry.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/video/beads-in-arizona\">10 minute documentary film from this eclipse</a></p> &amp;nbsp; <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00092A.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2671 aligncenter\" alt=\"DSC00092A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00092A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a>The mystique of the American southwest has always called to me.  This is my first experience in the Grand Canyon, and it did not disappoint!</p> </blockquote> I decided only a week before to chase this eclipse!  Was saving my dimes for the Total Eclipse in Australia later in the year.  And even though I do nothing but globe-trot to exotic locales - it does get expensive! But I made it happen.  And I was so richly rewarded for doing so.  The <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/video/beads-in-arizona\">documentary film</a> that come out of this expedition is worth every penny it cost me. <!--nextpage--> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00032A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2673\" alt=\"DSC00032A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00032A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00049A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2674\" alt=\"DSC00049A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00049A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">I\'m filming with my new video camera on this trip.  The <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/video/beads-in-arizona\">documentary film</a> I made of this eclipse is a must-see!</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00079A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2675\" alt=\"DSC00079A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00079A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Colorado River is the culprit here!</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00083A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2676\" alt=\"DSC00083A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00083A.jpg\" width=\"409\" height=\"544\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Eclipse chasers Chris and Liz Malicki.</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00094A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2678\" alt=\"DSC00094A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00094A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photography gets me excited.</p> </blockquote> <!--nextpage--> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00658A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2681\" alt=\"DSC00658A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00658A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00657A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2680\" alt=\"DSC00657A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00657A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00652A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2679\" alt=\"DSC00652A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00652A.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"298\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">All Sedona, all the time.</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00109A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2682\" alt=\"DSC00109A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00109A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is my eclipse day T!  Only put it on 18 times!  That\'s right - it\'s the Days Inn in Flagstaff.</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00628A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2687\" alt=\"DSC00628A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00628A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Chris Malicki watching the beginning of the eclipse.</p> </blockquote> <!--nextpage--> <p style=\"text-align: left;\">We chose a very specific GPS location as our observing site this time.  Just inside the southern limit of the eclipse path, we are able to see certain phenomenon not visible from the centre line.  These \'Baily\'s Beads\' occur only when the edge of the Moon grazes the edge of the Sun.</p> <p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/arizona-edge-path.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2726 aligncenter\" alt=\"arizona edge path\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/arizona-edge-path.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/annular_1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2689\" alt=\"annular_1\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/annular_1.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">As the Moon slides across the face of the Sun from bottom right to top left, you can easily see that the Moon\'s disc is slightly smaller than the Sun\'s.   That\'s why today\'s eclipse is not Total.</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00613A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2685\" alt=\"DSC00613A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00613A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Allan Connery doesn\'t miss a second of the action with his pro eclipse viewers!</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/annular_2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2690\" alt=\"annular_2\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/annular_2.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">As the Moon slides upward, it\'s clear we are near the edge of the path.  Very exciting!</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00610A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2684\" alt=\"DSC00610A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00610A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/annular_ring.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2695\" alt=\"annular_ring\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/annular_ring.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">The super-thin ring of an annular eclipse at the southern edge.  Beads abound where the Moon\'s edge grazes the Sun\'s at top right. <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/video/beads-in-arizona\">See the film here!</a></p> </blockquote> <!--nextpage--> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00614A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2686\" alt=\"DSC00614A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00614A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Chris gets up close and personal with the annular eclipse through his trusty scope.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/annular_4.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2691\" alt=\"annular_4\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/annular_4.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Moon continues its upward climb and breaks the ring.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/newspaper-shot.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2728\" alt=\"newspaper shot\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/newspaper-shot.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"417\" /></a></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Arizona Republic\'s Michael Chow captures this magical image of a few hikers in the right place, at the right time.</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSCN4408A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2693\" alt=\"DSCN4408A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSCN4408A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Whoohoo!  This is WAY better than golf!</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00629A.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2688\" alt=\"DSC00629A\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/DSC00629A.jpg\" width=\"601\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">Eclipse chasers May 20, 2012.  Liz Malicki, Chris Malicki, Allan Connery, Val Connery, eclipseguy.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/partial_sunset.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2694\" alt=\"partial_sunset\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/partial_sunset.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></a></p>  <blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: center;\">One of my favourite eclipse images of all time.  The still-partially-eclipsed sun setting over the desert horizon.</p> </blockquote> <p style=\"text-align: left;\">Tired of the razor-thin superficiality of your existence?  All done with reality shows and fatty foods?  Come eclipse chasing with me.  <a href=\" http://eclipseguy.dev/eclipse-calendar\">See where we are going next.</a></p>','Arizona - May 20, 2012',0,'The last-minute eclipse chase steeped in the mystique of the American southwest.  It don\'t get no betta!','publish','closed','closed','','arizona-may-20-2012','','','2013-02-17 04:03:48','2013-02-17 08:03:48','',0,'http://eclipseguy.dev/reports/arizona-may-20-2012',0,'reports','',0),(591,5,'2009-04-19 18:42:38','2009-04-19 22:42:38','','hots_thumb',0,'','inherit','open','open','','hots_thumb','','','2009-04-19 18:42:38','2009-04-19 22:42:38','',0,'http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/hots_thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(595,5,'2009-04-19 18:54:43','2009-04-19 22:54:43','Watch me on the news in South Australia talking        about the Moon\'s shadow over Lyndhurst on December 4, 2002.','Eclipseguy in the news in Australia!',0,'Catch me on the news in Australia! ','publish','open','open','','eclipseguy-in-the-news-in-australia','','','2012-06-05 23:46:35','2012-06-06 03:46:35','',0,'http://eclipseguy.dev/?p=595',0,'post','',0),(596,5,'2009-04-19 18:52:07','2009-04-19 22:52:07','','auzzy_news_thumb',0,'','inherit','open','open','','auzzy_news_thumb','','','2009-04-19 18:52:07','2009-04-19 22:52:07','',595,'http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/auzzy_news_thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(597,5,'2009-04-19 18:50:47','2009-04-19 22:50:47','Watch me on the news in South Australia talking        about the Moon\'s shadow over Lyndhurst on December 4, 2002.','Eclipseguy in the news in Australia!',0,'Catch me on the news in Australia! ','inherit','open','open','','595-revision','','','2009-04-19 18:50:47','2009-04-19 22:50:47','',595,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/595-revision',0,'revision','',0),(598,5,'2009-04-19 18:52:31','2009-04-19 22:52:31','Watch me on the news in South Australia talking        about the Moon\'s shadow over Lyndhurst on December 4, 2002.','Eclipseguy in the news in Australia!',0,'Catch me on the news in Australia! ','inherit','open','open','','595-revision-2','','','2009-04-19 18:52:31','2009-04-19 22:52:31','',595,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/595-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(599,5,'2009-04-19 18:53:14','2009-04-19 22:53:14','Watch me on the news in South Aust