ller film and video on this site!  \r\n\r\nLiving life so fully, so passionately, has been a true gift.  I am one of the luckiest people on Earth to have discovered something so enormous, so inspiring, that it has changed the course of my life.  \r\n\r\nAs a result, I live life on the fringe - outside the mainstream.  Whether it is my career as an independent artist or my deep passion for chasing eclipses, everything I do is unconventional.  The choices I have made in my life baffle my friends.  But I know who I am.  And I will go my own way no matter the cost.  \r\n\r\nI am heavily into music - cosmology - metaphysics - and art of all kinds.  I have gazillions of friends all over the world and value celebration, self-expression and community above all else.  Yup, I guess I am a bit of a bohemian.  When I am not chasing eclipses, playing guitar or reading, you can find me at Burning Man, at a yoga class or camping for the summer solstice.  \r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/portrait.jpg\" alt=\"dm portrait\" />\r\n','About Eclipseguy',0,'','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-30','','','2009-06-01 13:12:26','2009-06-01 17:12:26','',2,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/2-revision-30',0,'revision','',0),(1149,5,'2009-05-24 20:32:02','2009-05-25 00:32:02','<img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/toro_eclipse_about.jpg\" alt=\"toro_image_about\" />\r\n\r\nHow did IÂ  become an eclipse chaser?\r\n\r\nLike any good story, it begins with a girl.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I met Amy in the spring of 1991.Â  I was a wide-eyed and wild 28 year-old and she was beautiful, sophisticated and as moonstruck as I was.Â  It was love at first sight.Â  We would go for walks - chase Moonrise to the outskirts of the city - and exchange life stories about our connection to the Moon.Â  We had \'kindred Moon souls,\' she once wrote.Â  And how true that was.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Th