 16:58:52','&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"pitchman biz card\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/pitchman_card_1.jpg\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Since delivering my presentation at the Toronto TEDx Convention, I have been asked to speak at all kinds of meetings and on expeditions about our place in the universe - talking about what I have learned from two decades of eclipse chasing.  From this, my alter ego as \"The Pitchman For The Universe\" has taken shape.  Don\'t get me started!  In 2015, I am looking for opportunities to present my hour-long talk \"Partnering With The Universe.\"</p>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"dave talks at TED\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ted_talk_1.jpg\" />\r\n\r\nNuggets from the talk can be found under the \"Musings\" main navigation tab at the top of the page on this website.  You can view my TEDx video <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/video/my-presentation-at-tedx-toronto\" target=\"_self\">here</a> - view a primer video for my talk <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/22826936\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> - and download the flyer in pdf format <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/partnering_flyer2.pdf\">here</a>.\r\n\r\nTo inquire about booking The Pitchman For The Universe, leave a comment at the bottom of this page, or contact me <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/contact\" target=\"_self\">here</a>.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"dave talks at TED again\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ted_talk_2.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Partnering With The Universe</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For 24 years, David Makepeace has travelled the world to witness Total Solar Eclipses - a natural phenomenon that has been called the most spectacular event you can witness from Earth.</p>\r\n\"When the shadow of the Moon sweeps over us, we are brought into direct contact with a tangible presence that is awe-inspiring.  That there is a powerful relationship between us and the immense forces of the universe becomes undeniable.\"\r\n\r\nWhat possible relationship could you have to the universe?  How could it make a difference in your life?\r\n\r\nWith breathtaking film and video captured around the world at eclipse events, Makepeace takes us on a tour of our world and our solar system - widening the perspective on our lives as only an eclipse chaser can.  Discover how the simple beauty and mystery of our world can open the door to a greater awareness of what we are and our place in the universe.','Speaking Engagements',0,'The Pitchman For The Universe is out there!  Come see my inspiring presentation about our place in the universe.','publish','open','open','','speaking-engagements','','http://eclipseguy.dev/contact\nhttp://eclipseguy.dev/contact\nhttp://eclipseguy.dev/video/my-presentation-at-tedx-toronto\nhttp://vimeo.com/22826936','2015-03-24 16:33:06','2015-03-24 20:33:06','',0,'http://eclipseguy.dev/?p=2261',0,'post','',2),(2870,5,'2014-09-13 14:51:36','2014-09-13 18:51:36','<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Oct_2014_crescents.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2871\" alt=\"Oct_2014_crescents\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Oct_2014_crescents.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"611\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Map from Jay Anderson shows the magnitude of the partial eclipse from different locations.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I wouldn\'t travel very far to see a partial solar eclipse, and this time I don\'t have to!  Hopefully neither do you!  During a partial eclipse like this one, it doesn\'t get dark and you don\'t see the Sun\'s corona or the other visual phenomena you get with a total eclipse.  But it\'s still pretty cool to see the Moon eclipsing the Sun no matter what the circumstances.  If you can, don\'t let this opportunity pass you by.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Here are a few great sources of information about this event:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/eclipse/solar/2014-october-23\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.timeanddate.com/eclipse/solar/2014-october-23</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.shadowandsubstance.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.shadowandsubstance.com/</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://home.cc.umanitoba.ca/~jander/pse2014/PSE2014.htm \" target=\"_blank\">http://home.cc.umanitoba.ca/~jander/pse2014/PSE2014.htm </a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">And check out my awesome video showing a partially eclipsed Sun setting in Arizona in 2012!  Your view of the October 23 eclipse might look a little bit like this ...</p>\r\n<iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/106060871\" height=\"281\" width=\"500\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/106060871\">Heavens On The Horizon</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/eclipseguy\">eclipseguy</a> on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.\r\n\r\nSee how the shadow of the Moon creeps into the day side of the Earth during this event ...\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Oct_2014.gif\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2885 aligncenter\" alt=\"Oct_2014\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/Oct_2014.gif\" width=\"250\" height=\"270\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Wanna see one of the upcoming eclipses?  <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/eclipse-calendar\">See my Eclipse Calendar here.</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>','Partial Solar Eclipse October 23, 2014',0,'An eclipse for anyone! Find out how you can see October\'s partial solar eclipse. ','publish','open','open','','partial-solar-eclipse-october-23-2014','','http://vimeo.com/106060871\nhttp://eclipseguy.dev/eclipse-calendar','2014-09-13 14:55:08','2014-09-13 18:55:08','',0,'http://eclipseguy.dev/?p=2870',0,'post','',0),(2866,5,'2014-07-19 18:12:16','2014-07-19 22:12:16','_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"pitchman biz card\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/pitchman_card_1.jpg\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Since delivering my presentation at the Toronto TEDx Convention, I have been asked to speak at all kinds of meetings and on expeditions about our place in the universe - talking about what I have learned from two decades of eclipse chasing.  From this, my alter ego as \"The Pitchman For The Universe\" has taken shape.  Don\'t get me started!  In 2013, I am looking for opportunities to present my new, hour-long talk \"Partnering With The Universe.\"</p>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"dave talks at TED\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ted_talk_1.jpg\" />\r\n\r\nNuggets from the talk can be found under the \"Musings\" main navigation tab at the top of the page on this website.  You can view my TEDx video <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/video/my-presentation-at-tedx-toronto\" target=\"_self\">here</a> - view a primer video for my talk <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/22826936\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> - and download the flyer in pdf format <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/partnering_flyer2.pdf\">here</a>.\r\n\r\nTo inquire about booking The Pitchman For The Universe, leave a comment at the bottom of this page, or contact me <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/contact\" target=\"_self\">here</a>.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" alt=\"dave talks at TED again\" src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/ted_talk_2.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Partnering With The Universe</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For 20 years, David Makepeace has travelled the world to witness Total Solar Eclipses - a natural phenomenon that has been called the most spectacular event you can witness from Earth.</p>\r\n\"When the shadow of the Moon sweeps over us, we are brought into direct contact with a tangible presence that is awe-inspiring.  That there is a powerful relationship between us and the immense forces of the universe becomes undeniable.\"\r\n\r\nWhat possible relationship could you have to the universe?  How could it make a difference in your life?\r\n\r\nWith breathtaking film and video captured around the world at eclipse events, Makepeace takes us on a tour of our world and our solar system - widening the perspective on our lives as only an eclipse chaser can.  Discover how the simple beauty and mystery of our world can open the door to a greater awareness of what we are and our place in the universe.','Speaking Engagements',0,'The Pitchman For The Universe is on tour in 2014.  Come see my inspiring presentation about our place in the universe.','inherit','open','open','','2261-revision-45','','','2014-07-19 18:12:16','2014-07-19 22:12:16','',2261,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/2261-revision-45',0,'revision','',0),(2748,5,'2013-01-12 22:32:03','2013-01-13 02:32:03','Where will you be?\r\n<h3>2012</h3>\r\n<strong>May 20</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. East China Sea. Japan, N. Pacific. Western U.S.  <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/news/the-next-eclipse\" target=\"_self\">More on this.</a>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2012may20a.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>November 13</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 4:02. N. Australia. Pacific Ocean.  <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/news/total-eclipse-in-2012\" target=\"_self\">More on this. </a>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2012nov13t.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<h3>2013</h3>\r\n<strong>May 10</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. N. Australia. Pacific Ocean.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2013may10a.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>November 3</strong> - Hybrid Eclipse (Annular/Total). Atlantic Ocean. Central Africa.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2013nov03h.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<h3>2014</h3>\r\n<strong>April 29</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Australia. Southern Ocean.\r\n\r\n<strong>October 23</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. N. America.\r\n<h3>2015</h3>\r\n<strong>March 20</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 2:47. North Pole. Norwegian Sea.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2015Mar20T.GIF\" alt=\"TSE2015animation\" />\r\n<strong>September 13</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. S. Africa. Antarctica.\r\n<h3>2016</h3>\r\n<strong>March 9</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 4:09.  Sumatra, Borneo, Sulawesi, Pacific Ocean.\r\n<img src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2016Mar09T.GIF\" alt=\"sinclair animation 2016\" />\r\n<strong>September 1</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse.  Africa.  Indian Ocean.\r\n<h3>2017</h3>\r\n<strong>February 26</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Pacific. Chile. Argentina. Atlantic. Africa.\r\n\r\n<strong>August 21</strong> - THE NEXT GREAT AMERICAN ECLIPSE! TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 2:40. United States.\r\n<img src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/SE2017Aug21T.GIF\" alt=\"sinclair animation 2017\" />','Eclipse Calendar',0,'','inherit','open','open','','551-revision-48','','','2013-01-12 22:32:03','2013-01-13 02:32:03','',551,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/551-revision-48',0,'revision','',0),(2262,5,'2011-07-20 12:37:19','2011-07-20 16:37:19','Since delivering my presentation at the Toronto TEDx Convention, I continue to speak about our place in the universe at conventions, on expeditions and wherever people gather!','Speaking Engagements',0,'','inherit','open','open','','2261-revisi