ian Sea.\r\n<strong>September 13</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. S. Africa. Antarctica.\r\n<h3>2016</h3>\r\n<strong>March 9</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 4:09.  Sumatra, Borneo, Sulawesi, Pacific Ocean.\r\n<strong>September 1</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse.  Africa.  Indian Ocean.\r\n<h3>2017</h3>\r\n<strong>February 26</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Pacific. Chile. Argentina. Atlantic. Africa.\r\n<strong>August 21</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 2:40. United States.','Eclipse Calendar',0,'','inherit','open','open','','551-revision-42','','','2010-04-17 19:45:03','2010-04-17 23:45:03','',551,'http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/551-revision-42',0,'revision','',0),(2335,5,'2011-07-20 16:54:35','2011-07-20 20:54:35','<p>Where will you be?</p>\r\n<h3>2010</h3>\r\n<p><strong>January 15</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. Indian Ocean. Landfall in East Africa to Burma.  <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/news/spectacular-annular-eclipse-in-january-2010\"><br />\r\nMore.</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>July 11</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 5:20. South Pacific Ocean. Landfall through The Cook Islands, French Polynesia, Easter Island &amp; extreme southern Chili. <a href=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/uncategorized/total-solar-eclipse-of-11-july-2010\">More.</a></p>\r\n<h3>2011</h3>\r\n<p><strong>January 4</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. Europe. North Africa.<br />\r\n<strong>June 1</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. Greenland. High Arctic.<br />\r\n<strong>July 1</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. Southern Ocean. New Saros begins!<br />\r\n<strong>November 25</strong> - Partial Solar Eclipse. Antarctica.</p>\r\n<h3>2012</h3>\r\n<p><strong>May 20</strong> - Annular Solar Eclipse. East China Sea. Japan, N. Pacific. Western U.S.<br />\r\n<img src=\"http://eclipseguy.dev/wp-content/uploads/se2012may20a.gif\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>November 13</strong> - TOTAL Solar Eclipse. Max. Duration 4:02. N. Australia. Pacific Ocean.<br />\r\n<img src